Package: TensorEEG
Type: Package
Title: Physics-Constrained Tensor EEG Simulation and Covariance-Aware Augmentation
Version: 0.10.0
Authors@R: person("Yiming", "Shen", email = "yiming.shen001@umb.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Generates synthetic EEG data as 3rd-order tensors using
    physically constrained mixing matrices (Fibonacci grid, Graph
    Laplacian) and manifold dynamics (Lie algebra drift) to benchmark
    BCI algorithms; also provides the covariance-aware augmentation
    family used in the multi-dataset cross-session safety audit of
    Shen and Degras (2026), including amplitude-matched Euclidean
    perturbation (E0), log-Euclidean isotropic jitter (G0), empirical
    tangent Gaussian jitter (G1), log-Euclidean geodesic mixup (G2),
    Riemannian alignment (A0), a six-metric covariance fidelity audit,
    and manifest-based replay of synthetic stacks for reproducibility
    audits.
